# Software Requirements Specification (SRS) for DDAS Project

## 1. Introduction  
### 1.1 Purpose  
This document describes the software requirements for the DDAS Project, aiming to provide a comprehensive overview of the project's functionalities and non-functional requirements.

### 1.2 Scope  
This SRS outlines the functionality of the Digital Document Archiving System (DDAS). The system will allow users to archive, retrieve, and manage digital documents efficiently.

### 1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations  
- DDAS: Digital Document Archiving System  

### 1.4 References  
[List any applicable references]

### 1.5 Overview  
This document is structured to guide developers and stakeholders through the functional and non-functional requirements of the DDAS.

## 2. Functional Requirements  
- User Authentication  
- Document Upload  
- Document Retrieval  
- Document Deletion  
- Search Functionality  
- User Role Management  

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements  
- Performance: The system should handle 1000 concurrent users.  
- Security: All data must be encrypted during transit.  
- Usability: The system should have an intuitive user interface.

## 4. System Architecture  
A high-level overview diagram will be provided, showing the components of the system and their interactions.

## 5. Database Schema  
- **Users Table**:  
  - user_id (PK)  
  - username  
  - password_hash  

- **Documents Table**:  
  - document_id (PK)  
  - user_id (FK)  
  - document_path  

## 6. Use Cases  
- Use Case 1: User Login  
- Use Case 2: Upload Document  
- Use Case 3: Retrieve Document  

## 7. Acceptance Criteria  
- All functional requirements must be implemented and tested.  
- Performance benchmarks must be met.

## 8. Deployment Strategy  
- The deployment will follow a CI/CD approach, utilizing cloud services to ensure high availability and scalability.

